{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f953f636-231b-4eb9-aefc-dc2031ae189e","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aac5b5fb-a8d4-409a-9895-bab1e5348929","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"0432:C2AE2:18FF19F:1C58BA2:69E82035"},"id":"74878c54-de7b-4f06-a5cf-da8fe8a344cf","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:11:22.809Z","parentId":"da35c02f-b229-46aa-bca8-76451fac6957"}
